00:40:04.390 --> 00:40:07.007
have a zero at the
end of a number?

00:40:07.007 --> 00:40:08.340
AMIR ACZEL: That's a good point.

00:40:08.340 --> 00:40:09.839
AUDIENCE: Is that
a different issue?

00:40:09.839 --> 00:40:10.400
I don't know.

00:40:10.400 --> 00:40:12.050
Maybe it happened at the
same time, maybe it didn't.

00:40:12.050 --> 00:40:12.620
I don't know.

00:40:12.620 --> 00:40:13.370
AMIR ACZEL: Right.

00:40:13.370 --> 00:40:15.810
I see what you're saying, right.

00:40:15.810 --> 00:40:16.910
I don't know.

00:40:16.910 --> 00:40:18.934
I have no answer to that.

00:40:18.934 --> 00:40:20.260
Sorry.

00:40:20.260 --> 00:40:22.220
AUDIENCE: If I
understand correctly,

00:40:22.220 --> 00:40:26.370
you dated this to 683
because of the text 605.

00:40:26.370 --> 00:40:30.500
But do you have evidence that
that text wasn't written years

00:40:30.500 --> 00:40:31.550
later?

00:40:31.550 --> 00:40:34.450
AMIR ACZEL: Right, so
that's a very good question.

00:40:34.450 --> 00:40:37.780
The temple there was
built around that time.

00:40:40.640 --> 00:40:44.610
Around 683, and we know
that from stylistic forms

00:40:44.610 --> 00:40:50.220
on the door frames, lintels,
and all these things there.

00:40:50.220 --> 00:40:53.800
So that site was
studied extensively

00:40:53.800 --> 00:40:55.880
by Coedes and by others.

00:40:55.880 --> 00:40:57.560
So we know when it was built.

00:40:57.560 --> 00:41:00.770
So for example, yeah,
that's how you know.

00:41:00.770 --> 00:41:03.790
So we know when the
temple was built.

00:41:03.790 --> 00:41:11.160
So maybe it's-- well, 683,
they wouldn't write it before

00:41:11.160 --> 00:41:13.434
